.TH GWEAVE 1 "2026-06-21" "GWEB" "GWEB Manual"
.SH NAME
gweave \- typeset a GWEB literate program as a TeX document
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gweave
.RB [ \-o
.IR dir ]
.IR file [ .w ]
.RI [ change [ .ch ]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B gweave
is the
.I weave
half of GWEB, a literate\-programming system for Go modeled on CWEB. It turns a
GWEB source file
.RI ( .w )
into a plain\-TeX document with pretty\-printed Go code (bold reserved words,
italic identifiers, typewriter strings), linked section references, and an
automatically generated index, list of section names, and table of contents. It
is the Go analogue of CWEB's
.BR cweave (1).
.PP
The woven document is written to the input's base name with a
.B .tex
extension. It begins with
.B \einput gwebmac
\(em
.B gweave
supplies this line itself \(em so the
.B .w
file need not. Process the result with a TeX engine that can find
.IR gwebmac.tex :
.PP
.RS
.EX
pdftex file.tex          # -> file.pdf, with hyperlinks and bookmarks
.EE
.RE
.PP
For the DVI route, request the dvipdfmx hyperlink back end with
.BR \elet\epdf+ ,
exactly as in CWEB:
.PP
.RS
.EX
tex "\elet\epdf+ \einput file.tex"
dvipdfmx file.dvi        # -> file.pdf, with hyperlinks and bookmarks
.EE
.RE
.PP
A plain
.B tex
run with no
.B \epdf
produces a DVI without links. The
.B .w
extension may be omitted
.RB ( gweave
.B wc
weaves
.IR wc.w ),
as may a change file's
.B .ch
extension. As it runs,
.B gweave
prints a brief progress report to standard error, one
.BI * N
per starred (chapter) section.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-o " dir"
Write the
.B .tex
file to
.I dir
instead of the input file's directory.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B TEXINPUTS
Point this at GWEB's
.B tex
directory (or copy
.I gwebmac.tex
next to your document) so the TeX engine can find the macro package. The
installer places
.I gwebmac.tex
in your TeX tree so this is not normally needed.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gtangle (1),
.BR pdftex (1),
.BR dvipdfmx (1),
.BR cweave (1)
.PP
The GWEB manual and source: <https://github.com/sjnam/gweb>.
